    <p>LONDON • Manch­ester United striker Edin­son Ca­vani has been charged with an ag­gra­vated breach of the Foot­ball As­so­ci­a­tion’s rules for us­ing the word “negrito” in an In­sta­gram post last month.</p>
    <p>The Uruguay in­ter­na­tional de­fended the term as an af­fec­tion­ate greet­ing as it is not con­sid­ered of­fen­sive in Latin Amer­i­can con­text.</p>
    <p>He has un­til Jan 4 to re­spond to the charge, which car­ries a three-game ban.</p>


